22 July The Government Communication and Information System in partnership with Agape Youth Movement will host a Mandela Month panel discussion on active and responsible citizenry. The panel discussion is aimed at developing a strong moral code in individuals and discuss the importance of creating a safe, supportive society while protecting democracy and to instil the values as embodied by the former late President Mandela and celebrate his legacy. Members of the media are invited to attend and cover the panel discussion. Details are as follows:   Date: Friday, 23 July 2021 Time: 14:00 – 15:00 Platform: Zoom (Webinar ID: 916 3634 4486 | Password: 064870) Panellists: Live streaming platform: Twitter: https://twitter.com/GCISMedia Enquiries: Tshegofatso Modubu Cell: 083 276 0786